
Davis: Radical Changes, Deep Constants is a book by Noteworthy Published Authors local author John Lofland.  A 160 page paperback published on October 2004, the ISBN is 9780738524641.

The description on the book reads, Placed on the map by the California Pacific Railroad in 1868, Davis has been radically different things over its thirteensome decades: wheatgrowing village, almond cultivation center, university farm locale, urbanizing town, exploding suburb, progressive community, and university city. Yet throughout these changes Davis remained the same in many ways, among them its efforts to retain a small town character and a vital downtown.
